A Star Point Pattern (42)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0\deflang1033\deflangfe1042{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}{\f1\fmodern\fprq2\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par \b Black to Play.\b0
\par Black cuts with 1 and white defends by making a hanging connection at 2. White is disregarding the pattern.
\par
\par \pard\nowidctlpar\qj Instead of 2, it is the correct move for white to capture the black stone with \b\f1 A\b0\f0 .
\par \pard
\par How should black punish white?
\par }
