Diagram 2 (Don't Be Afraid of a Pae)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}{\f1\fmodern\fprq2\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par In response to black \'a1\'e3, if white resists at 1, black captures a white stone with 2.
\par
\par \pard\nowidctlpar\qj Wherever white plays, black will still capture at \b\f1 A\b0\f0 .
\par \pard
\par You should play like this to overcome your opponent.
\par
\par Please do not forget this.
\par }
